The Euclidean algorithm is: to find gcd(a, b), repeatedly replace the larger number with the remainder when divided by the smaller, until one is zero. The non-zero one is the gcd. So a function like this:

int gcd(int a, int b) {
    while (b != 0) {
        int temp = a % b;
        a = b;
        b = temp;
    }
    return a;
}

